author: Zachary Dewei Yang
text:
Located in Oasis Terraces Level 1, straight ahead after you see KFC, Anytime Fitness Punggol Oasis is one of the best Anytime Fitness(AF) in the whole of Singapore. To get to AFOasis you can take the East Line LRT from Punggol MRT and alight at Oasis stop. This is the most convenient way to get to the gym.

Recently renovated, AFOasis is gym to many of the Punggol Residents in the whole of Punggol. It is a place for personal growth and exploration. There are three toilets with bidet and showering facilities. Out of the three toilets, one is designated for female members and coach. You can store your bags and belongings in one of the many lockers available, get your workout locked in, shower and head straight to work or shopping!

There are various equipments to meet your fitness routines and goals. There are two areas in the gym,the air conditioned Indoor where the isolation machines, cable flys, lats machine, dumbbells, fixed bar bells, smith machine, squat racks, power lifting platform, cardio machines and toilets are located. There is also a water cooler located near the vending machine and lockers.

There is an Outdoor Patio for warm- ups, calisthenics, boxing, cardio dancing, kettle bells, weighted balls, training mats and boxes for your use and training routine.

As a member of Anytime Fitness Oasis, you can sign up for training classes such as Hyrox, Muay Thai and Zumba. Checkout the AFOasis IG page for better information and updates!

Anytime Fitness is also an international gym membership! After the initial month, you can access ALL Anytime Fitness in Singapore from Punggol to Jurong! So if you‚Äôre staying at your partner‚Äôs place, I am sure that an Anytime Fitness is around the corner, NO EXCUSES! GET YOUR WORKOUT LOCKED IN!

And when you‚Äôre travelling for work or leisure, there will always be an Anytime Fitness near your hotel! Like the name, it is opened 24 HRS and 365 days.

If you‚Äôre new and unsure how to start your fitness journey, you can speak to the Gym Manager Daniel and his team of Coaches, Joel and Damia. Manager Daniel is friendly and approachable. He is also an experienced coach. Share with them your fitness goals and they will help you build your workout routine tailored for your schedule. Once you‚Äôre comfortable on being on your own, you will find this cosy gym like your second home. Special shoutouts to Carlos and the Owner of the Gym!

Come and get a free gym session or tour if you‚Äôre in Punggol! Make AFOasis your Gym! A place where you become the best version of yourself! A place where friendships are forged through sweat, tears and growth!

PS. After your workout, you can head down to NTUC to get your meal prep groceries or head up to the food court to fuel your growth and recovery! There are also many eateries like KFC, Encik Tan, MacD, Subway and Starbucks.

I hope you will love this gym as much as I do!

author: Munny L
text:
Upon entering you'll be identified, the gym has 1 locker and 1 cubby shelf. 1 female dedicted washroom and 3 washrooms in total. Hair drying spot at the corner of the corridor. Soap is well stocked and provided. They also have a vending machine with protein and a standard water cooler.

They have every machine needed!
A dedicated spot for a couple of Treadmills, ellipticals, bicycles and 1 stair master
Weightlifting area is in the middle with:
2 squat racks and 1 smith machine
Free weights, barbells
2 leg press machines
Bench presses
Adductor machine
2 bench press machines
Row, lat pull machine, chest fly, shoulder press, leg curl, leg extension
Cable machine with pull up bar

Though there's not alot of walking space in the whole gym, so users really stand close to each other.

Best part of OasisAF is the outdoor patio that's equipped with kettle bells, yoga mats and a huge space to workout in. They have a cable machine outdoors. A row machine and a (not so popular) back extension bench. The patio is surrounded by mirrors. It's closed to users when there are group classes going on from time to time.

There's no inbody machine for weight measurement, but just your good old traditional weighing machine.

author: Calvin Tan
text:
My ‚ÄúWanton Mee‚Äù Trainer- Troy.

I want to extend my deepest appreciation to my Personal Trainer Mr Troy Tan for the incredible transformation I‚Äôve experienced under his guidance.

When I began this journey, my goals were clear: to lose weight and regain my long lost body fitness by building strength across key muscle groups. Thanks to Troy‚Äôs tailored workouts, unwavering encouragement, and deep understanding of fitness and body mechanics, I‚Äôve not only achieved those goals but exceeded my own expectations.

To be frank, I wasn‚Äôt 100% convinced signing up PT at AF was the right decision for me in the past. Before meeting Troy, there was this long-lingering self-doubt on my own physical fitness being able to match up to a PT‚Äôs ‚Äúdemands‚Äù. Before knowing Troy, the PT in my mind was the less than ideal image PTIs often portray from NS days. It isn‚Äôt hard for many to identify our NS days‚Äô PTIs being stern, authoritative, and even condescending.

Thankfully, Troy is nothing like the said above. He has the right technical skills matched with the right soft skills. He has the complete package - the brains, the physique, and the handsome face to match (envy).

Troy has a rare ability to push just the right amount‚Äîchallenging me without overwhelming me, motivating without pressuring. His consistency, professionalism, and positive energy made every session something I looked forward to, and his holistic approach to fitness helped me build healthier habits beyond the gym.

He matches science to psychology. He knows the human mind to a point I wonder why wasn‚Äôt he a clinical psychologist. He knows what one is thinking for that little nudge when one is thinking of giving up. He pushes your limits in a non-invasive way, a way so natural until I myself don‚Äôt even know I had actually improved from my last personal best.

His care goes beyond the confines of the gym space. He embraces overall nutrition with what food nutrition and lifestyle changes I needed to make. I still recall in the earlier sessions when he asked what I had for lunch. His face (I still remember that face) when I told him ‚Äúwanton mee‚Äù spoke a thousand words. Maybe it‚Äôs what one can relate casually as ‚Äúbombastic side eye‚Äù. This simple wanton mee was enough to trigger a candid whole conversation of what foods to avoid and why.

Expectations vs Results: I recall I gave myself a 6 months timeline to achieve my weight loss and fitness targets. A short 3-4 weeks in, I started having people around me going ‚ÄúYou lost weight!‚Äù, ‚ÄúYou look better now. What did you do?‚Äù, and of course ‚Äúthe tummy is gone!‚Äù. Nothing proves results than such remarks to match the better breathing and ‚Äúlightness‚Äù I myself felt during this journey. A whole 2 months in to today, I have also advanced to needing a whole new wardrobe change (woohoo!).

Lastly, I am glad I did this first step 2 months ago. Getting to know Troy and the AF Oasis crew changed my life. I thereby wholeheartedly recommend Troy to anyone serious about reaching their fitness goals. His dedication and skill make him truly exceptional.

Thank you!

author: Arvind Aaswani
text:
I had a regrettable experience with Anytime Fitness last year. Opting for a 1-year contract seemed enticing, but I soon discovered there was no option to cancel before the term ended. Despite not using their services, the gym showed no interest in my attendance until the membership was about to expire.

Throughout the year, they never inquired about my absence, but as my membership expiration neared, they aggressively pursued renewal with enticing offers. Declining the renewal, they then insisted on a hefty SGD 99.14 cancellation fee, showcasing their focus on financial gains rather than member well-being.

The lack of communication and support for members who weren't actively attending raises concerns about their priorities. My advice: take your time before signing any agreements, as some gyms seem more interested in membership numbers than promoting a healthy lifestyle.

author: Michael Scott
text:
The gym provides sufficient equipment for your exercising needs and you'd have a good time if you join with the foundational mentality that you're paying for a gym without staff because of how ill-trained and feedback-resistant the general staff are.

Over time, you'll witness the general lack of care from staff about the gym and they spend more time having fun and chatter in the office than making sure the place is operating at peak environment. Throughout the time period of covid, measures were not upheld, patrons without masks everywhere chatting with each other. You'll see fellow patrons without towels leaving sweat puddles on benches and staff not bothering with this gym 'rule'. Writing in to staff, you often meet more confrontational personalities than common-sense, customer-oriented approaches.

If you're able to get beyond the state of the general staff, you'd have a decent workout here.

author: Charlotte (11pmposts)
text:
Gym is alright, with outdoor space. Administration has a lot of room for improvement. It‚Äôll be difficult for u to pause on holiday unlike other anytime outlets if u sign up here. They charge at the 1st of every month so u can‚Äôt pause anytime between the month if u already paid.

Eg. If u booked a travel on 18th Sept
-U can only pause if it‚Äôs done before September

U can‚Äôt do impromptu trips and u must inform them way in advanced because they only process it when they have time for it and not on the dates u requested for.

They only pause when they have time to look at ur emails (that is not within the few days of sending) and they don‚Äôt reply sometimes unless you keep prompting. So
You will also need to be the one to constantly follow up on them/ WhatsApp them to remind them on this because they don‚Äôt reply ur emails.

The staff replying on whatspp is friendly and replies within a day but he/she isn‚Äôt the one in charge of pausing ur membership and can do nothing on it.

A lot of room for improvement for thegym administration to streamline the process and they also need to state or have clearer instructions on what‚Äôs required from the member‚Äôs end for pauses as they don‚Äôt tell u before that. So, there‚Äôs a lot of back and forth for such an easy process.

Frustrating to deal with, would recommend signing with a different branch for an easier fuss-free experience.

text:
Here is my review for Anytime fitness Oasis outlet, after 8 months of joining them.

Reason for joining- Although, I do have a small gym in condo, but I wanted to get Personal Trainer for some time, and hence joined a gym nearby to my place.

Personal Trainer - Good experience while training with Darren. We went through multiple changes in training schedule to figure out what best suites me.

Gym interior - Really outdated and demotivating, seriously need a revamp and proper structuring of quipments.

Equipments quality - I can say it‚Äôs ok, and an area of improvement.

Equipments availability - Rack and benches are really low in number. Again the placement of equipments makes it a congested place, specially during peak hours, this is a major area of improvement.

Bathroom, changing and locker facilities - Below standard and should be improved with proper changing rooms and toilets.

This was not established earlier and the staff blamed it on not reading the agreement. I read it and it said it had to be done in writing which was done so via whatsapp. What is the point of BLATANTLY asking for a renewal if it is to be of no use.

Staff was EXTREMELY rude and interrogative. If i could give 0 or negative reviews, i would. If the general manager or whosoever, and not the staff that handled this matter as it was clearly not handled well, contact me. This is utterly unacceptable and inappropriate. This could have been handled in a much MUCH better way. I am extremely enraged and disappointed. I hope something is done about the staff and i will never engage this outlet ever again.

author: Hansel
text: Thank you for the feedback Hansel. As a business, we need to ensure that we cater to the needs of all members, and allocate the limited space on the gym floor between free weights, stacked weights, cardio, functional training etc. Besides the equipment mandated by the franchisor, we also invested in additional pieces of equipment, which perhaps made the gym a little more cramped. However, we believe most members appreciate the fact that we tried our best to provide more value to them. In respect of the equipment layout, we had actually consulted with and leveraged the expertise of the top equipment suppliers in Singapore to make the layout as efficient as possible. That said, if you have any specific suggestion for improving the equipment alignment, please let us know! :)
